fields.descriptive_line:
Set of wooden and rubber parts to make soldiers  made in England by Tri-ang in the 1930s
[Torso] 10 wooden torsos, part of a set to make soldiers. Made in England by Tri-ang in the 1930s
[Arms] Arms for toy soldiers, made of wood. Part of a set of soldiers made in England by Tri-ang in the 1930s
[Legs] Leg of a toy soldier. Made in England by  Tri-ang in the 1930s
[Heads] Head for toy soldiers, made of wood. Part of a set of soldiers made in England by Tri-ang in the 1930s
[Rifles] Rifles for toy soldiers, made of wood. Part of a set of soldiers made in England by Tri-ang in the 1930s
[Shoes] Shoes for toy soldiers, made of wood. Part of a set of soldiers made in England by Tri-ang in the 1930s
[Hats] Hat for toy soldiers, made of wood. Part of a set of soldiers made in England by Tri-ang in the 1930s
[Long Pipe] Length of terracotta coloured rubber pipe. Used in the set of toy soldiers to connect the wooden parts.
[Short Pipes] 81 pieces of short, terracotta, rubber pipe. Used in the set of toy soldiers to connect the wooden parts.
fields.physical_description:
A set of toy soldiers consisting of 81 loose rubber parts, 10 hats, 10 heads, 10 torsos, 20 legs, 21 arms, 23 shoes and 7 rifles.
[Torso] Red painted wooden rectangles with deliberate holes and indentations in. 
[Arms] Wooden arms painted red. Hole at one end and cut at the other. 
[Legs] Wood painted blue. Deliberate holes on either end.
[Heads] Painted wooden egg shaped heads with deliberate holes and indentations in. Black painted hair and painted faces. Varnished. 
[Rifles] Wooden rifles, possibly stained a darker brown than they were initially. 
[Shoes] Wooden rifles, painted black with an indentation on the top of each one. 
[Hats] Wooden hats for toy soldiers, painted black with a half-hollow inside and an indentation.
[Long Pipe] Length of terracotte coloured rubber pipe.
[Short Pipes] 81 short lengths of terracotta, rubber pipes.
